Class Variable

  • public class Variable

    A variable is a simple expression with a name (like "x") and a settable value.

        public static Variable make(java.lang.String name)
        Return a unique variable named `name'. There can be only one variable with the same name returned by this method; that is, make(s1) == make(s2) if and only if s1.equals(s2).
        Parameters:
        name - the variable's name
        Returns:
        the variable; create it initialized to 0 if it doesn't yet exist
